# Forms & Data

## INSTRUCTION RULES
- Use framework-native form handling with Zod validation. Do not add a separate form library unless the project already uses one.
- The API layer MUST always be fully typed. Use whatever the project provides (orval, tRPC, typed fetch wrappers). If none exists, create typed fetch functions with Zod response validation.
- Prefer the simplest solution with the fewest abstraction boundaries. Do not add unnecessary layers between the API and the UI.
- ALL user-facing strings MUST be i18n-ready. Do not hardcode user-visible text — use translation keys or a string constants file, depending on the project's i18n setup.
